				Well what can I say, an excellent rewrite to an already superlative guide.<BR>
I read your first edition of this guide, and began to upgrade my warriors AC. By acquiring pieces of Royal Velium armour, and some very nice 6AC 65hp rings, I now have nearly 650AC and 1000hp for my lvl 24 warrior. I noticed a massive increase in his survivability with this focus on AC and truly believe its the way warriors should go. I was interested to read your latest comments about str, and as a barbarian, I currently only have about 140str (yeah i read some dodgy character creation guides, so i put points in a mix of str, agi and sta, rather than dumping it all in str). I shall have to concentrate on boosting my str up some more, to increase my damage output :)<BR>
I also encountered many of the problems you have mentioned, such as lack of CR abilities, and total inability to travel anywhere, etc etc. <BR>
It was truly exasperating to read that the guys at verant think that warriors are overpowered! Have they no idea what its like to play one?!? Your compiled suggestions of abilities for a warrior really hit home, and I particularly like the one of the master of disciplines. One of the main problems with a warrior, is the grinding monotony of auto attack, taunt, slam. Perhaps with the implementation of some nice lower level disciplines, on seperate timers recycling per game day, a warrior could be more effective and fun to play. <BR>
I eagerly await the next installment, from the source of information on all things warrior :)
